          <statement>
            <p>
              <m> k(x)=\ln(x)</m>.  Evaluate at <m>x=100</m>.
            </p>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <p>
              <m>k'(x)=1/x</m>.   So <m>k'(100)=0.01</m>. The numeric derivative agrees to 13 decimal digits.
            </p>
